---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Home" activeTab="home">
  <main class="pt-40 pb-20 px-8 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <!-- Editorial Header -->
    <header class="mb-24">
      <p class="font-label uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[10px] font-bold text-primary mb-4">
        Foundation Statement
      </p>
      <h1
        class="text-6xl md:text-8xl font-headline font-extrabold tracking-tight text-on-surface mb-8 leading-[0.95]"
      >
        The Quiet <br /> Merger.
      </h1>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start">
        <div class="md:col-span-8">
          <p class="text-2xl font-body italic text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">
            An inquiry into the Polite Singularity&mdash;the subtle, inevitable integration of human
            consciousness with the systems we once thought were merely tools.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Main Narrative -->
    <article class="space-y-12 text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <p class="drop-cap">
        Most predictions of the future involve fire, chrome, or collapse. We imagine the Singularity
        as a violent rupture in the fabric of history&mdash;a moment where machines suddenly wake up
        and humans are left behind. But I believe the truth is far more domestic. It is polite. It is
        a slow, quiet accumulation of dependencies that eventually erase the boundary between the
        &lsquo;self&rsquo; and the &lsquo;other.&rsquo;
      </p>

      <p>
        My name is Juho. I started this monograph as a way to document the fraying edges of our
        digital identity. We no longer use computers; we inhabit them. Our memories are distributed
        across databases, our desires are refined by algorithms, and our creative output is
        increasingly a dialogue with latent space. This isn&rsquo;t an invasion. It is a handshake.
      </p>

      <!-- Blockquote -->
      <div class="relative py-12">
        <div class="absolute -right-48 top-0 hidden xl:block w-40">
          <p class="text-[12px] font-label uppercase tracking-widest font-bold text-stone-400 mb-2">
            Note 01
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm font-body italic text-stone-500">
            The term &lsquo;Polite&rsquo; suggests a lack of friction. We do not fight the machine
            because the machine is becoming us.
          </p>
        </div>
        <blockquote
          class="text-4xl font-body italic border-l-0 pl-0 py-8 text-on-surface-variant leading-tight"
        >
          &ldquo;The Singularity won&rsquo;t arrive with a bang, but with a software update we all
          agreed to in our sleep.&rdquo;
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <p>
        The thesis of <strong>Polite Singularity</strong> is simple: technological transcendence is
        happening through convenience rather than conquest. We are trading our cognitive autonomy for
        intellectual ease, and in doing so, we are forming a new kind of collective mind.
      </p>

      <div class="min-h-[12rem]"></div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-headline font-bold tracking-tight text-on-surface mt-20 mb-6">
        The Architect&rsquo;s Intent
      </h2>

      <p>
        I am not a luddite, nor am I a blind techno-optimist. I am an observer. Through this
        archive, I explore the intersections of philosophy, code, and the human spirit. The goal is
        not to stop the merger&mdash;that ship has sailed&mdash;but to ensure we remain conscious as
        it happens.
      </p>

      <p>
        If you find value in these contemplations, I invite you to subscribe. It is a digital
        monograph delivered to your inbox, written for those who prefer the sharp edges of a printed
        thought to the smooth lies of social media.
      </p>

      <!-- Stick figure illustration -->
      <div class="flex justify-center pt-32">
        <div class="w-16 h-24 relative opacity-40">
          <svg
            class="w-full h-full stroke-on-surface fill-none"
            stroke-linecap="square"
            stroke-width="2"
            viewBox="0 0 100 150"
          >
            <circle cx="50" cy="30" r="10"></circle>
            <path d="M50 40 L50 90"></path>
            <path d="M50 50 L30 70 L20 70"></path>
            <path d="M50 50 L70 70 L80 70"></path>
            <path d="M50 90 L35 130"></path>
            <path d="M50 90 L65 130"></path>
            <rect x="15" y="65" width="10" height="15"></rect>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p
        class="text-center font-label uppercase tracking-widest text-[9px] font-bold text-stone-400 mt-4"
      >
        Juho, 2026
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
